  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "The structural skeleton of a dub rhythm: short pitch envelope builds the punch, slow LFO filter wobble builds the pocket. Everything here is about the groove, not the space. The architecture before the echo chamber.",
  "tags": [
    "overdub",
    "dub",
    "groove",
    "rhythmic",
    "foundation",
    "structure",
    "transcendental"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OVERDUB — Temporal Evolution and Degradation-as-Architecture",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-21",
    "scripture": [
      "Scripture VII-1: The Dry Groove Is the Groove"
    ],
    "revelation": "The groove must live in the dry signal. If the echo is doing the work, the groove is already dead.",
    "diagnosis": "Groove Architecture tests OVERDUB's pitch envelope as a rhythmic tool. At moderate velocity the pitch dive is subtle; at full velocity it becomes the accent. The LFO wobble adds a lazy human pocket without chaos."
  },
